Class XmlDocumentList

java.lang.Object
  org.cast.cwm.xml.XmlDocumentList
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<XmlDocument>
public class XmlDocumentList
extends Object
implements Iterable<XmlDocument>

An ordered list of XmlDocument objects. This class supports some convenient operations over a whole set of XML documents, such as locating pages (or in general, Label counts) that are numbered sequentially over several files.

getByLabel

public XmlSection getByLabel(Serializable label,
                             int num)
Get the XmlSection for the Nth label from this ordered list of XmlDocuments. As with XmlDocument.getByLabel(Serializable, Integer), the count starts from 0 and goes in document order. In this case, it continues on to each document in the list until the given N is reached.

Parameters:
label - which label category to use
num - (N) the index to retrieve
Returns:
the XmlSection, or null.
